data.event: Major G.M. Price, a land speculator, laid out the town in 1837.

event.title: was founded by the Shepard family in 1849

data.event: At Pleasant Ridge, one of the first African-American communities in Wisconsin was founded by the Shepard family in 1849 and settled in the 1850s.
Lancaster calls itself "The City of the Dome" after the octagonal glass and copper-clad dome of its courthouse building, which was designed by Armand Koch and built in 1905.
